Blues for Smoke is an album by pianist Jaki Byard recorded in 1960 and released on the Candid label.1
Reception
Allmusic awarded the album 4&lt;U+00BD&gt; stars with its review by Scott Yanow stating, &quot;A highly recommended outing from a very underrated pianist&quot;.2
Track listing
All compositions by Jaki Byard
&quot;Journey/Hollis Stomp/Milan to Lyon&quot; - 5:57
&quot;Aluminum Baby&quot; - 4:32
&quot;Pete and Thomas (Tribute to the Ticklers)&quot; - 3:41
&quot;Spanish Tinge No 1&quot; - 4:12
&quot;Flight of the Fly&quot; - 5:44
&quot;Blues for Smoke&quot; - 4:52
&quot;Jaki's Blues Next&quot; - 2:07
&quot;Diane's Melody&quot; - 5:05
&quot;One Two Five&quot; - 2:40
Personnel
Jaki Byard - piano
